LEGIONELLOSIS - EUROPE (02): FRANCE (OCCITANIE) FATAL, RECURRENCE
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sun 16 Apr 2017, 9:13 AM
Source: Metropolitain [in French, trans. Corr.SB, edited]
http://e-metropolitain.fr/2017/04/16/palavas-les-flots-encore-un-cas-de-legionellose/


A new case of legionellosis led to hospitalization at the Montpellier CHU [Centre Hospital Universitaire] of a tenant of the residence of La Nouvelle Vague, on the road to Carnon, east of Palavas-les-Flots. He is out of danger, according to the Regional Health Agency-Occitania.

In June [2016], 3 tenants of the residence contracted this acute lung infection, with 1 death and 2 emergency hospitalizations, including a patient who had been in a coma for several days.

Surveys of hot water pipes and other appliances that equip the homes of the residence have been under way since June [2016] and have been relaunched after this new case of legionellosis.

[Byline: Jean-Marc Aubert]

